description: Acts as a viroporin and self-assembles in host membranes forming pentameric protein-lipid pores that allow ion transport.
Stimulates NSP14(3'-5' exoribonuclease) and NSP16(2'-O-methyltransferase) activities.
Modulates host cell survival signaling pathway.
Role in the initial induction of autophagosomes from ER (DMV formation).
Could be a determinant of virus virulence.
